The paper deals with fundamental limits for problems in multiterminal data compression, network coding, and multimedia transmission, which are all related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also utilizes tools and algorithms from abstract algebra to efficiently determine supports for joint probability mass functions, which is a topic in computer science theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves numerical optimization, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses information geometry, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with multimedia transmission, which is a topic in multimedia systems and applications (cs.MM).
